I didn't want her dead. See?
You understand what I'm saying?
I'm not in anything.

1436
01:22:14,713 --> 01:22:18,577
- You choose her over the show?
- Of course I do! Yes!

1437
01:22:18,646 --> 01:22:22,272
You think it's right some
tootsie walks in and messes up
a beautiful thing like this?

1438
01:22:22,314 --> 01:22:25,007
- I wanted a great play
as much as you did.
- No, not as much.

1439
01:22:25,080 --> 01:22:27,511
- But you don't kill for it!
- Yeah? Who says?

1440
01:22:27,579 --> 01:22:30,943
My father used to listen to the opera.
He loved the opera. But if a guy stunk--

1441
01:22:31,013 --> 01:22:33,774
- What, he killed him?
- One time, in Palermo.

1442
01:22:36,946 --> 01:22:41,708
I'm an artist too, not great
like you, but you know what?
First I'm a human being.

1443
01:22:41,780 --> 01:22:45,304
- I'm a decent, moral human being.
- What are you doin' with
Helen Sinclair then?

1444
01:22:45,347 --> 01:22:48,540
- What has that got to do
with it? How did you know?
- Everybody in town knows.

1445
01:22:48,613 --> 01:22:51,079
Except maybe your girlfriend.
Who you think you're foolin'?

1446
01:22:51,314 --> 01:22:54,746
I might not be perfect, but you're
a killer! You're a degenerate animal!

1447
01:22:54,813 --> 01:22:57,973
You're a murderer! You b--
You belong in the electric chair!

1448
01:22:58,013 --> 01:23:00,672
Listen to me, you.
You listen to me.

1449
01:23:00,746 --> 01:23:04,042
Nobody, nobody is gonna
ruin my work, you hear me?

1450
01:23:04,280 --> 01:23:06,041
Nobody, huh?

1451
01:23:16,513 --> 01:23:19,480
I've fallen in love
with Helen Sinclair...

1452
01:23:19,546 --> 01:23:23,479
and I lied to you about it
the other day, which I'm sure
that you probably knew.

1453
01:23:23,546 --> 01:23:26,842
I want to let you know I didn't mean
for this to happen. It just happened.

1454
01:23:26,880 --> 01:23:28,869
I'm not surprised.
She is extraordinary.

1455
01:23:28,946 --> 01:23:32,037
- So are you. It's me
that's all screwed up.
- I have a confession to make.

1456
01:23:32,280 --> 01:23:35,939
You knew the whole time,
but you were too damn decent
to confront me while I was--

1457
01:23:36,013 --> 01:23:39,002
No, I've been seeing
Sheldon Flender.

1458
01:23:39,080 --> 01:23:41,978
- Pa-Pa-Pardon me?
- We've been having an affair.

1459
01:23:42,013 --> 01:23:45,843
- Did you say Sheldon Flender?
- Yes, he's been in love
with me for a long time.

1460
01:23:45,913 --> 01:23:48,902
Do you know his theory that art
is relational, that it requires two--

1461
01:23:48,980 --> 01:23:50,946
the artist
and the audience?

1462
01:23:50,980 --> 01:23:53,003
- He feels that way about sex too.
- About-- About sex?

1463
01:23:53,080 --> 01:23:56,308
Yes, between the two right people,
it can become an art form.

1464
01:23:56,380 --> 01:24:00,539
Are you saying that you and
Flender have raised intercourse
to the level of an art form?

1465
01:24:00,613 --> 01:24:02,545
Not just intercourse.
Foreplay too.

1466
01:24:02,613 --> 01:24:05,307
- My friend, the unproduced playwright?
- He's been after me a long time.

1467
01:24:05,347 --> 01:24:09,608
You never seem to want to get married,
and so, one night we went out,
had a few drinks...

1468
01:24:09,680 --> 01:24:12,976
and started discussing art
and literature and Freud and Nietzsche.

1469
01:24:13,013 --> 01:24:15,843
And in order to illustrate
a point on Greek etymology...

1470
01:24:15,913 --> 01:24:17,845
I noticed he'd
unbuttoned his fly--

1471
01:24:17,913 --> 01:24:21,277
No, no, no, no! Please, please!
I don't need to hear any more.

1472
01:24:21,314 --> 01:24:24,711
But he's a major talent. You've
said so yourself a million times.

1473
01:24:24,780 --> 01:24:28,735
With an intellect that big, you tend
to create your own moral universe.

1474
01:24:45,447 --> 01:24:47,379
[ Knocking ]

1475
01:24:50,946 --> 01:24:53,605
- I just wanted to wish you good luck.
- Oh, darling.

1476
01:24:53,680 --> 01:24:56,805
You look pale.
No, no, not to worry.

1477
01:24:56,846 --> 01:25:01,505
Soon this town will belong to you.
We're having dinner Sunday night
with Gene O'Neill.

1478
01:25:01,579 --> 01:25:05,568
He's heard that your writing
is morbid and depressing.
He's dying to meet you.

1479
01:25:05,646 --> 01:25:07,578
- Oh, here's that brush.
- I know you'll be terrific tonight.

1480
01:25:07,646 --> 01:25:10,908
Oh! They're your words.

1481
01:25:10,980 --> 01:25:13,071
I'm just a vessel.

1482
01:25:13,314 --> 01:25:15,973
You fill me.

1483
01:25:16,013 --> 01:25:19,536
And this? This is
just the beginning.

1484
01:25:19,613 --> 01:25:24,545
I've been discussing all kinds of new
ideas for vehicles for me with my agent.

1485
01:25:24,613 --> 01:25:27,579
There's a variety of women
I can play. As you get to know me...

1486
01:25:27,646 --> 01:25:30,340
you'll see there's no limit
to my range.

1487
01:25:30,414 --> 01:25:33,641
They say that I can
still play late twenties...

1488
01:25:33,680 --> 01:25:36,976
but I say no, no,
thirty tops.

1489
01:25:37,013 --> 01:25:39,774
We'll go to my house
in the Vineyard. It's quiet there.

1490
01:25:39,846 --> 01:25:42,438
You can write.
I'll bring you coffee.

1491
01:25:42,480 --> 01:25:44,968
Listen, you better go.
I-I-It's 15 minutes to curtain.

1492
01:25:45,047 --> 01:25:47,535
I still haven't done
my breathing exercises yet.

1493
01:25:47,613 --> 01:25:50,773
Y-Y-You-- Fate.
Fate has thrown us together.

1494
01:25:52,780 --> 01:25:54,712
Merde.

1495
01:25:55,813 --> 01:25:57,745
[ Gasps, Sighs ]

1496
01:25:58,813 --> 01:26:01,336
[ Gasps, Sighs ]

1497
01:26:01,414 --> 01:26:05,505
[ Dramatic Panting ]

1498
01:26:11,314 --> 01:26:13,405
Take him.
Take him!

1499
01:26:13,480 --> 01:26:16,843
Let him leave me bereft,
without a penny. Go ahead. Take him.

1500
01:26:16,880 --> 01:26:20,404
But don't think it'll last forever.
The same thing'll happen to you.

1501
01:26:20,480 --> 01:26:24,435
Sylvia, I don't know
why you're so unhappy.

1502
01:26:24,513 --> 01:26:26,741
- Why you're such
a deeply unhappy person...
- Oh, God!

1503
01:26:26,813 --> 01:26:29,711
- but I want you to know that--
- Because you're taking my husband...

1504
01:26:29,780 --> 01:26:33,076
my life, the very core
of my being, you stupid idiot!

1505
01:26:33,314 --> 01:26:35,779
- I didn't ever mean to hurt you. I--
- [ Footsteps ]

1506
01:26:35,846 --> 01:26:38,812
Oh, Edgar.

1507
01:26:38,846 --> 01:26:41,607
- I've just been speaking
with Dr. Philips.
- Yes.

1508
01:26:41,680 --> 01:26:46,612
Her explicit instructions are
that we, none of us,
leave the premises as of today.

1509
01:26:46,680 --> 01:26:49,078
- [ Horse Neighing ]
- [ Nick ] How's she workin'?

1510
01:26:49,314 --> 01:26:51,075
[ Man ]
Good. Good, boss.

1511
01:26:53,013 --> 01:26:54,979
Out this morning.

1512
01:26:56,447 --> 01:26:59,503
- Cheech.
- What's up, Mr. V.?

1513
01:26:59,579 --> 01:27:03,978
Uh, nothin'.
I just wanted to talk.

1514
01:27:04,047 --> 01:27:06,013
- Yeah?
- I'm a little sad these days.

1515
01:27:06,047 --> 01:27:08,877
- Sure. Yeah.
- You know how it is.

1516
01:27:14,513 --> 01:27:17,638
Curtain's gone up already.
Poor kid.

1517
01:27:18,846 --> 01:27:20,812
Would've been a star,
don't you think?

1518
01:27:20,846 --> 01:27:24,778
Yeah. It's all right.
We'll take care of those Kustabeck guys.

1519
01:27:24,846 --> 01:27:28,642
- I wonder if it really was
the Kustabecks.
- Well, who else?

1520
01:27:28,713 --> 01:27:33,271
I don't know.
But we got some tips...

1521
01:27:33,347 --> 01:27:36,074
- that Charlie K. had
nothin' to do with this.
- Really.

1522
01:27:36,314 --> 01:27:39,075
Yeah. Don't make
no sense anyhow.

1523
01:27:39,314 --> 01:27:43,371
I mean, the way things
were coolin' off and all.

1524
01:27:43,447 --> 01:27:46,038
I'll see what I can find out
on the street, ya know?

1525
01:27:46,280 --> 01:27:49,768
- Where you rushin' off to?
- Hey, you know, I told
the guys in the show...

1526
01:27:49,846 --> 01:27:52,505
that I, uh, I'd stop by
and wish 'em good luck.

1527
01:27:52,579 --> 01:27:55,410
- I got friendly with
some of the stage hands.
- Did you?

1528
01:27:55,480 --> 01:27:57,536
- Yeah.
- That's unlike you.

1529
01:27:57,613 --> 01:27:59,545
- Why's that?
- Unless they shoot crap.

1530
01:27:59,613 --> 01:28:02,875
No, you know, you see
the same faces every day. You know.

1531
01:28:04,880 --> 01:28:08,972
Marty Bannister said he saw you pick
up Olive the night she got it, Cheech.

1532
01:28:09,047 --> 01:28:11,979
- Me?
- Didn't you tell me you didn't see her?

1533
01:28:12,013 --> 01:28:13,979
Me? Yeah,
I said I did.

1534
01:28:14,013 --> 01:28:18,775
I picked her up, and I dropped her off
a few blocks from the theater. Why?

1535
01:28:18,846 --> 01:28:21,812
- You had nothin' against Olive, did ya?
- Olive? Naw.

1536
01:28:21,880 --> 01:28:24,903
- I like Olive. Why?
- I mean, you got along well?

1537
01:28:24,980 --> 01:28:27,276
Olive and l, we got along good.
You know, Olive.

1538
01:28:27,347 --> 01:28:29,279
Olive was good for
a lot of laughs, right?

1539
01:28:29,314 --> 01:28:31,506
- Except for a few tiffs here and there?
- Right.

1540
01:28:31,579 --> 01:28:33,568
Olive's-- You know.
We got along.

1541
01:28:35,380 --> 01:28:38,312
How come you didn't bring her
to me at the club, Cheech?

1542
01:28:38,347 --> 01:28:42,302
She said you changed your mind, that
I should drop her off at the theater.

1543
01:28:42,347 --> 01:28:45,972
- The theater. At night?
- Yeah. Yeah.

1544
01:28:46,013 --> 01:28:49,309
There was no preview
that night, Cheech. No rehearsal.

1545
01:28:49,380 --> 01:28:51,641
Really?

1546
01:28:51,713 --> 01:28:54,873
How come you
left her alone, Cheech?

1547
01:28:54,946 --> 01:28:57,639
- [ Laughs ]
- And you didn't come
to the club and tell me?

1548
01:28:57,713 --> 01:29:01,543
I'm gonna level with you, all right?
I had a crap game.
I didn't want to miss it.

1549
01:29:01,613 --> 01:29:03,909
- Mmm.
- Yeah.

1550
01:29:03,980 --> 01:29:07,378
- Why you don't tell me?
- You wanna lay off?
I'm up to here in debts.

1551
01:29:07,447 --> 01:29:09,379
- I'm tryin' to get even.
- Yeah?

1552
01:29:09,447 --> 01:29:12,606
Yeah. Dice ain't been too lucky for me.
You know. You know how it is.

1553
01:29:12,646 --> 01:29:15,771
You keep tellin' me I gotta quit.
Ya know, I should.

1554
01:29:15,846 --> 01:29:17,778
- Cheech--
- Listen, listen.

1555
01:29:17,813 --> 01:29:21,041
I told the guys I'd wish them good luck
in the show. They're very superstitious.

1556
01:29:21,280 --> 01:29:24,303
I'm gonna find out who hit her,
all right? I'll find out.

1557
01:29:24,380 --> 01:29:26,471
All right.
I'll see ya later.

1558
01:29:31,579 --> 01:29:34,568
He did it, Nick.
I don't know what his grudge was.

1559
01:29:34,646 --> 01:29:37,306
Maybe they were
two-timin' ya.

1560
01:29:37,347 --> 01:29:39,869
- What are you sayin' to me?
- Take it easy, Nick.

1561
01:29:39,946 --> 01:29:43,071
It's only a guess.
But Marty Bannister saw them together...

1562
01:29:43,314 --> 01:29:45,745
and that pier is
Cheech's favorite spot.

1563
01:29:45,813 --> 01:29:48,643
Can't you see he was lyin', Nickie?
Did you see the look on his face?

1564
01:29:48,713 --> 01:29:52,907
- He was scared.
- Look, Nick, I know you
don't like to think it...

1565
01:29:52,980 --> 01:29:56,639
- but the gossip is, she
was runnin' around on ya.
- Don't say that!

1566
01:29:56,680 --> 01:29:59,476
- I'm only tryin' to help, Mr. V.
- Nickie.

1567
01:29:59,546 --> 01:30:01,479
He's only tryin'
to help.

1568
01:30:03,080 --> 01:30:05,012
Cheech and Olive.

1569
01:30:06,447 --> 01:30:08,503
Fix him.

1570
01:30:08,579 --> 01:30:12,273
Oh, it's goin' great.

1571
01:30:12,314 --> 01:30:16,507
Yeah, they're eating it up. Before,
I could smell money. Now I can taste it.

1572
01:30:16,579 --> 01:30:18,977
- [ David ] Mmm, yeah.
- Hey, what's the matter?

1573
01:30:19,047 --> 01:30:22,445
You look as though you're watchin'
a turkey. It's just the opposite.

1574
01:30:22,480 --> 01:30:25,912
- Where's Ellen?
- Oh, she was too nervous to come.

1575
01:30:25,980 --> 01:30:28,775
[ Warner ] This is
Dr. Emilene Philips, a family friend.

1576
01:30:28,813 --> 01:30:30,938
- Hey. How's it goin'?
- Cheech, how are ya?

1577
01:30:31,013 --> 01:30:34,604
Goin' great. Wonderful.
You need to cheer him up. I don't know.

1578
01:30:34,680 --> 01:30:36,646
- What's the matter?
- What do you want?

1579
01:30:36,680 --> 01:30:39,771
- It's goin' great, huh?
- You killed Olive, Cheech.

1580
01:30:39,813 --> 01:30:41,904
For that I can never
forgive you.

1581
01:30:41,980 --> 01:30:44,741
I don't care what kind of
genius you are.

1582
01:30:44,813 --> 01:30:48,575
Listen to that audience. Huh? They got
'em right in the palm of their hand.

1583
01:30:48,646 --> 01:30:51,510
Hey, Cheech. It's over for you.
You're finished.

1584
01:30:51,579 --> 01:30:53,511
[ Eden ] I had such
a wonderful time.

1585
01:30:53,579 --> 01:30:57,875
[ Ellen ] I can't live like this,
the same routine over and over.

1586
01:30:57,946 --> 01:31:01,810
You think the same thing's not gonna
happen to you as happened to me?

1587
01:31:01,846 --> 01:31:04,835
You think you're not gonna be here
sitting with a hole in your sweater...

1588
01:31:04,913 --> 01:31:06,845
and a drink in your hand
someday?

1589
01:31:06,913 --> 01:31:10,402
- Just wait!
- Cheech! You should be out front.

1590
01:31:10,480 --> 01:31:13,570
You're about to miss my great scene.
Did you see the first part?

1591
01:31:13,646 --> 01:31:18,578
- How did it go?
Do you think they like it?
- [ Cheech ] Great, great.

1592
01:31:18,646 --> 01:31:22,942
- Where's Cheech?
- Get the fuck outta here.
Get outta here.

1593
01:31:23,013 --> 01:31:26,570
- Sucker.
- [ Play Dialogue
Continues lndistinctly ]

1594
01:31:28,980 --> 01:31:32,037
- You crapped out for
the last time, Cheech.
- [ Eden ] I think he's--

1595
01:31:32,280 --> 01:31:35,405
I'm in the garden, Sylvia,
tending roses.

1596
01:31:35,480 --> 01:31:38,604
[ Helen ] Oh, darling,
if we just had a baby.

1597
01:31:38,680 --> 01:31:42,306
- That's all I think about.
- [ Warner ] We've been
through all this before.

1598
01:31:42,380 --> 01:31:45,539
[ Panting ]
Cheech! Cheech.

1599
01:31:45,613 --> 01:31:47,772
David.

1600
01:31:47,813 --> 01:31:50,938
- [ Straining ] The last line...
- Yes?

1601
01:31:51,013 --> 01:31:52,979
in the play.

1602
01:31:54,347 --> 01:31:57,608
Tell Sylvia Poston...

1603
01:31:59,613 --> 01:32:02,273
to say she's pregnant.

1604
01:32:03,913 --> 01:32:07,504
It'll be a great finish.

1605
01:32:07,579 --> 01:32:10,739
- Oh, God, that's so great.
- No. Don't speak.

1606
01:32:12,414 --> 01:32:14,346
Don't speak.

