01:32:16,347 --> 01:32:23,541
##

1608
01:32:23,613 --> 01:32:27,478
"A masterpiece."
"A theatrical stunner."

1609
01:32:29,780 --> 01:32:32,712
"A work of art
of the highest quality.

1610
01:32:32,780 --> 01:32:36,076
One of the greatest moments of this
reviewer's experience was in Act III...

1611
01:32:36,314 --> 01:32:38,905
when the Lieutenant returns
and confronts his mistress.

1612
01:32:38,980 --> 01:32:41,639
We hear distant gunshots,
which get louder and louder...

1613
01:32:41,713 --> 01:32:46,442
bringing the Lieutenant's twisted
military past and violent tendencies...

1614
01:32:46,513 --> 01:32:48,570
into bold bas-relief.

1615
01:32:48,646 --> 01:32:53,477
Writer-director David Shayne
is the find of the decade.

1616
01:32:53,513 --> 01:32:56,968
- Where is David?
- I don't know. I assumed he'd be here.

1617
01:33:12,680 --> 01:33:14,703
Flender!

1618
01:33:14,780 --> 01:33:17,440
Flender, wake up.
It's David Shayne.

1619
01:33:17,513 --> 01:33:19,809
I need
to talk to you.

1620
01:33:19,846 --> 01:33:23,370
Please, Flender.
Flender!

1621
01:33:23,447 --> 01:33:26,810
Ha-ha! Look who's here.
The big Broadway success.

1622
01:33:26,846 --> 01:33:28,971
I don't write hits.
My plays are art.

1623
01:33:29,047 --> 01:33:31,774
- They're written specifically
to go unproduced.
- Is Ellen there?

1624
01:33:31,813 --> 01:33:33,870
- No, she's not here.
- I think she is.

1625
01:33:33,946 --> 01:33:36,469
Congratulations
on your hit, David.

1626
01:33:36,513 --> 01:33:39,604
- I always knew ya had it in you.
- Yeah, well, you were wrong.

1627
01:33:39,646 --> 01:33:42,771
- I have to--
I have to ask you a question.
- What?

1628
01:33:42,813 --> 01:33:45,473
Did you love me as the artist
or as the man?

1629
01:33:45,546 --> 01:33:49,535
- Both.
- Well, what if it turned out
that I wasn't really an artist?

1630
01:33:49,613 --> 01:33:52,478
I could love a man if
he's not a real artist...

1631
01:33:52,546 --> 01:33:55,377
but I couldn't love an artist
if he's not a real man.

1632
01:33:55,447 --> 01:33:58,606
Th-This is all academic.
She's with me now. You're with me now.

1633
01:33:58,680 --> 01:34:01,374
- Do you really want to be with Flender?
- Yes.

1634
01:34:01,447 --> 01:34:04,413
- Hey! Flender is a great lover.
- Ohh.

1635
01:34:04,480 --> 01:34:08,844
- Hey, I slept with Flender.
He was just okay.
- [ Ellen ] Really?

1636
01:34:08,913 --> 01:34:11,572
[ Flender ] Rita, please!
What are you talking about?

1637
01:34:11,646 --> 01:34:13,578
That was years ago, during
your free-love period.

1638
01:34:13,646 --> 01:34:16,635
[ Ellen ] I feel it's relational.
For me, he's great.

1639
01:34:16,713 --> 01:34:19,941
Huh, interesting. Are you talking
pure mechanics or what?

1640
01:34:20,013 --> 01:34:22,479
- His technique is prodigious.
- [ Flender ] Prodigious?

1641
01:34:22,513 --> 01:34:26,775
- You're confusing sex and love.
